by Kiu Ghesik » Wed Sep 23, 2020 5:17 pm

The Caleshan Valkyrie put the theory of mechanized, walking heavy weapons carriers into practice with mechs called "Direwolves". These mechs can travel incredibly fast, carry a wide variety of payloads, and stand about head height. I imagine they'd likely be used as "patrol boats" or "go-fasts" to compliment the Caleshan "aircraft carrier" land-ships, as opposed to support units for fireteams of soldiers, though, given their speed and mobility that would quickly leave an unaugmented human behind. If these things are mass-producible, though, that's terrifying. Wolf-like hunters able to withstand modern weaponry and proficient in the use of heavy weaponry would be devastatingly effective combatants up close and from afar.
